nciThesaurus.definition: A genetically-engineered protein formed by the fusion of prostatic acid phosphatase (PAP) and sargramostim (GM-CSF). Vaccination with antigen-presenting cells (APC) loaded with prostatic acid phosphatase-sargramostim fusion protein may elicit a cytotoxic T-cell response against tumor cells that express PAP. (NCI05)
nciThesaurus.preferredName: Prostatic Acid Phosphatase-Sargramostim Fusion Protein PA2024
synonyms: PROSTATIC ACID PHOSPHATASE (PAP)-GRANULOCYTE-MACROPHAGE COLONY-STIMULATING FACTOR (GM-CSF) FUSION PROTEIN
